article.headline: Montana fumble return in OT sends Idaho St. to a 33-27 loss

images.name: Wild 40-yard fumble return gives Montana the OT victory
images.caption: Montana S Eric Johnson recovers Idaho State's last-minute fumble and returns it 40 yards to the house for the game-winning touchdown in overtime.

article.linkText: Montana fumble return in OT sends Idaho St. to a 33-27 loss
article.story: POCATELLO, Idaho -- JR Nelson pounced on a bad snap in overtime and tossed the ball to Eric Johnson, who raced 40 yards for the winning touchdown as Montana escaped Idaho State with a 33-27 win Saturday. Montana (5-4, 4-2 Big Sky) held a 24-13 lead after three quarters, but Idaho State rallied with a pair of fourth-quarter touchdowns to take a 27-24 lead. Daniel Sullivan tied the game at 27-27 with 5:43 left with a 26-yard field goal to send the game into overtime. The Bengals (2-7, 1-5) won the toss and Montana turned the ball over on a Makena Simis fumble on its possession in OT. Idaho State attempted a 27-yard field goal to win the game, but the snap sailed wide right and Nelson won a footrace for the loose ball. Nelson picked off a Tanner Gueller pass and returned it for a touchdown in the second quarter.

videos.headline: Wild 40-yard fumble return gives Montana the OT victory
videos.description: Montana S Eric Johnson recovers Idaho State's last-minute fumble and returns it 40 yards to the house for the game-winning touchdown in overtime.
